                <head>239. Editorial note</head>
                <p>On November 16, 1976, the <persName corresp="#p_FGR1">Ford</persName>
                    Administration approved the grant of $400,000 in communications equipment and
                    training for the Government of Sudan. The Sudanese Government had requested the
                    grant for equipment and training to combat terrorism, counter foreign plots
                    against the country, and improve its international communications abilities. The
                    proposal was considered by the Operations Advisory Group on November 8, which
                    unanimously recommended it to President <persName corresp="#p_FGR1"
                        >Ford</persName>, who signed the finding. (<persName corresp="#p_SB3"
                        >Scowcroft</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_FGR1">Ford</persName>,
                    November 16; National Security Council, <persName corresp="#p_FGR1"
                        >Ford</persName> Administration Intelligence Files, Subject Files, Box 13,
                    Sudan)</p>
            </div>
